answerText: Under the Greenwood Tree or The Mellstock Quire: A Rural Painting of the Dutch School[10] Under the Greenwood Tree is the first in this author's "Wessex" series of novels, which also includes The Return of the Native and The Mayor of Casterbridge.

question: Question: The original title of this work was going to be The Mellstock Quire. For 10 points each: [10] Name this novel in which choir member Dick Dewy becomes attracted to schoolmistress Fancy Day. The vicar Mr. Maybold also eventually proposes marriage to Fancy.
